WEBVTT

00:14:27.294 --> 00:14:30.135
AG: Kat had been
at the company just two years.

00:14:30.159 --> 00:14:32.596
Helping turned out to be
an incredibly efficient way

00:14:32.620 --> 00:14:34.421
to build her expertise,

00:14:34.445 --> 00:14:36.572
especially because she was
in an organization

00:14:36.596 --> 00:14:38.404
where good work got noticed.

00:14:38.428 --> 00:14:42.420
Hooters wasn't exactly known
as the go-to place for making connections.

00:14:42.768 --> 00:14:44.792
But they were growing exponentially,

00:14:44.816 --> 00:14:47.506
opening up new restaurants
all over the place.

00:14:47.530 --> 00:14:49.352
KC: There weren't Wharton MBAs

00:14:49.376 --> 00:14:51.474
beating down the doors
to go work at Hooters.

00:14:51.498 --> 00:14:55.926
And so they had to look within
to find their talent.

00:14:55.950 --> 00:14:58.958
I was receiving a disproportionate number

00:14:58.982 --> 00:15:01.712
of development and growth
opportunities in that company,